      "text": "Air Conditioner Structure Description - Compressor"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "Feature"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The A/C compressor is driven by a belt and functions as a pump to circulate the refrigerant. The compressed refrigerant becomes a hot, high-pressure gas and is sent to the condenser. The compressor is equipped with a mechanical relief valve that activates when the refrigerant pressure exceeds a predetermined value. The activated relief valve cannot be reused and must be replaced."
    },
